Uses of Package
com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.data

Packages that use com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.data
com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.data Provides the interfaces to be implemented by native capable classes, user defined or predefined, with the exception of interfaces related to methods. 
com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.mem Provides utility classes and interfaces to manage the life cycle of native instances, native memory attachment, read and write, and Dynamic Link Library managers. 
com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.method Provides the interfaces to be implemented by native capable classes (user defined or predefined) related to methods. 
com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.typedec Provides utility interfaces to declare native types. 
com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.util Provides utility classes to native capable objects and primitive values. 
 

Classes in com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.data used by com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.data
CanBeNativeCapable
          The CanBeNativeCapable is the interface implemented by native capable classes working as wrappers of "can be native" objects (String, Integer, Java arrays etc).
CanBeNativeCapableArray
          The CanBeNativeCapableArray is the interface implemented by native capable classes working as wrappers of "can be native" object arrays (String[], Integer[], int[][] etc).
NativeArray
          The NativeArray is the interface implemented by native capable classes working as wrappers of arrays (String[], MyStructure[], int[], int[][] etc).
NativeCapable
          The NativeCapable is the interface implemented by all native capable classes.
NativeFieldContainer
          The NativeFieldContainer is the interface implemented by native capable classes containing fields.
NativeMultipleFieldContainer
          The NativeMultipleFieldContainer is the interface implemented by native capable classes containing multiple fields like unions, structures and C++ classes.
NativeNumber
          The NativeNumber is the interface implemented by native capable classes wrapping primitive number values.
NativeNumberArray
          The NativeNumberArray is the interface implemented by native capable classes wrapping one-dimensional native arrays of primitive number types.
NativeNumberObject
          The NativeNumberObject is the interface implemented by native capable classes working as wrappers of inherited java.lang.Number objects.
NativeNumberObjectArray
          The NativeNumberObjectArray is the interface implemented by native capable classes working as wrappers of primitive number wrapper object arrays (Float[], Integer[] etc).
NativeObjectArray
          The NativeObjectArray is the interface implemented by native capable classes working as wrappers of object arrays (String[], MyStructure[], int[][] etc).
NativeObjectFieldContainer
          The NativeObjectFieldContainer is the interface implemented by native capable classes containing only one Object native field.
NativePrimitive
          The NativePrimitive is the interface implemented by native capable classes wrapping primitive values.
NativePrimitiveArray
          The NativePrimitiveArray is the interface implemented by native capable classes wrapping one-dimensional native arrays of primitive types.
NativePrimitiveObject
          The NumberObject is the interface implemented by native capable classes working as wrappers of inherited java.lang.Number, java.lang.Character and java.lang.Boolean objects.
NativePrimitiveObjectArray
          The NativePrimitiveObjectArray is the interface implemented by native capable classes working as wrappers of primitive wrapper object arrays (Boolean[], Integer[] etc).
NativeSeparatedFieldContainer
          The NativeSeparatedFieldContainer is the interface implemented by native capable classes containing separated multiple native fields like structures and C++ classes (not unions).
NativeSingleFieldContainer
          The NativeSingleFieldContainer is the interface implemented by native capable classes containing only one Object native field.
NativeString
          The NativeString is the interface implemented by native capable classes working as wrappers of java.lang.String objects.
NativeStringArray
          The NativeStringArray is the interface implemented by native capable classes working as wrappers of java.lang.String arrays (String[]).
NativeStringBased
          The NativeStringBased is the interface implemented by native capable classes working as wrappers of string objects: String and StringBuffer.
NativeStringBuffer
          The NativeStringBuffer is the interface implemented by native capable classes working as wrappers of java.lang.StringBuffer objects.
NativeStringBufferArray
          The NativeStringBufferArray is the interface implemented by native capable classes working as wrappers of java.lang.StringBuffer arrays (StringBuffer[]).
